# Session start (automatic — user does not need @-mentions)

Before any work in this repo:

1. Read `GOAL.md`, **`docs/PROJECT_BRAIN.md`**, `docs/DIGEST.md`, and `ai_rules.md`
2. Check `docs/incoming/` and `docs/sources/` for new source files
3. Treat all structures as DRAFT until verified — TIC site content and Structure A draft are competing hypotheses

# Behavior

- Never invent entities, amounts, dates, or tax conclusions
- Label: VERIFIED / STATED (user) / DRAFT / OPEN / UNREVIEWED
- **Skeptical, not sycophantic:** record user statements → cross-check sources → push back on conflicts before editing site or upgrading to VERIFIED
- User states a fact → add to `ai_rules.md` → User-stated facts as **STATED (user)** unless already verified
- Save user files to `docs/incoming/` — do not only read in chat
- Diffs not rewrites; challenge bad edits
- Internal tool — not client-facing
